<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     04-28 0729</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0754</SECOND>
<HEAD>Strong Thunderstorms Over Midwest, Winter In The Rockies</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Strong thunderstorms developed over parts of Iowa and Missouri
today, while snow continued to pile up in the Rockies.
   Storms on Thursday produced scattered tornadoes in Iowa and
Nebraska, officials said.
   One twister swooped down within 1,000 yards of Bluffs Run
greyhound race track in Council Bluffs, Iowa, sending track patrons
scrambling for cover, officials said. One man was injured when he
was struck in the head by debris and required stitches, a security
guard said.
   In a separate incident, Jerry Ostendorf, operations chief for
the Iowa Office of Disaster Services, said a woman was injured when
a mobile home was overturned in Corning, a town in southwestern
Iowa.
   A security guard at Bluffs Run said he climbed into a ditch as
the twister passed overhead.
   ``I grabbed a pretty sturdy tree in the ditch and I could feel
the pressure pulling up on me,'' said James Wanner, 23, of Council
Bluffs. ``I felt the hair on my arms standing up. We were pretty
scared.''
   Showers and thunderstorms today were over southeast Nebraska,
northeast Kansas, central Illinois, central Indiana, southern
Wisconsin and southern Minnesota.
   A few showers and thunderstorms were also over south-central
Texas and southeastern Louisiana.
   Omaha, Neb., received an inch and a half of rain in the six
hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT, while Springfield, Ill., had about an
inch and a quarter of rain. Des Moines recorded nearly an inch
during the same period.
   Snow fell across parts of Montana and Wyoming, with up to 14
inches in northeastern Wyoming. Billings, Mont., Casper, Wyo., and
Lander, Wyo., all received 2 inches of snow in the six hours ending
at 2 a.m. EDT.
   On Thursday, thunderstorms produced wind gusts to 66 mph in Des
Moines and to 70 mph in Norwalk, Iowa.
   Hail the size of tennis balls was reported in Ipava, Ill.
   Meantime, a heat wave Thursday produced several record
temperatures for the date in the South and Midwest, including:
Apalachicola, Fla., 86 degrees; Charleston, S.C., 94; Concordia,
Kan., 93; Daytona Beach, Fla., 93; Evansville, Ind., 91; Fort
Smith, Ark., 91; Grand Island, Neb., 95; Kansas City, Mo., 90;
Lincoln, Neb., 95; Nashville, Tenn., 91; Norfolk, Neb., 92; Omaha,
Neb., 92; Paducah, Ky., 89; St. Louis, Mo., 92; Sioux Falls, S.D.,
90; Sioux City, Iowa, 91; and Springfield, Mo., 91.
   Today's forecast: showers and thunderstorms scattered from the
Mississippi Valley across the upper Great Lakes and much of the
lower Ohio Valley to the North Carolina coast; numerous
thunderstorms from the middle Mississippi Valley to the lower Ohio
Valley; rain spreading across the northern Plains and Nebraska as
well as northern Utah and southern Idaho; and snow from the
northern Rockies to the upper Missouri Valley.
   High temperatures were to be in the 30s across much of Wyoming
into western South Dakota; in the 40s and 50s from the northern and
central Rockies across the northern Plains, much of Nebraska, the
upper Mississippi Valley and much of the Great Lakes to northern
New England; in the 80s and low 90s from all of Texas except the
Panhandle across the lower Mississippi Valley, Missouri, the
Tennessee Valley,the Gulf Coast region and the southern
Appalachians to the southern Atlantic Coast and Florida, the desert
Southwest and inland valleys of southern California.
   Highs in much of the rest of the nation were to be in the 60s
and 70s.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 24
degrees in Yellowstone Park in Wyoming to 77 degrees in Key West,
Fla.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 68 fair; Boston 45 fair; Buffalo 38 fair;
Charleston, S.C., 73 fair; Cincinnati 61 partly cloudy; Cleveland
48 cloudy; Detroit 48 cloudy; Miami 70 fair; New York 50 fair;
Philadelphia 54 fair; Pittsburgh 49 fair; Portland, Maine, 42
cloudy; Washington 60 partly cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 42 rain; Chicago 53 cloudy; Dallas-Fort Worth
71 fair; Denver 36 fair; Des Moines 59 foggy; Indianapolis 61
cloudy; Kansas City 67 cloudy; Minneapolis-St. Paul 46 showers;
Nashville 68 fair; New Orleans 71 partly cloudy; St. Louis 75 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 47 fair; Anchorage 46 cloudy; Las Vegas 57
fair; Los Angeles 57 fair; Phoenix 64 fair; Salt Lake City 42
showers; San Diego 58 fair; San Francisco 51 fair; Seattle 51 fair.
   _Canada: Montreal 37 cloudy; Toronto 32 fair.
