<HEAD>Will Vice Stars Be Iced? No One's Saying</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Miami Vice is gone, but is it curtains for its main
characters? No one will say.
   The television drama that made the city's Art Deco enclaves and
neon-pastel ambiance world famous closed shop Thursday night when
the final scene was shot in Miami Beach.
   The plot is strikingly similar to the original show, aired Sept.
16, 1984. The main characters, detectives played by Don Johnson and
Philip Michael Thomas, are sent to the fictional South American
country of Costa Morado to bring back a corrupt dictator to testify
against international drug traffickers.
   The secret is the ending. Officials at NBC are not saying
whether the detectives, Sonny Crockett and Rico Tubbs, will be
killed off when they make their last stand. The set was closed to
visitors.
   The show is scheduled to air May 21.
