<HEAD>Body Of Young Man Found In Rubble Of Cemetery Bell Tower</HEAD>
<DATELINE>URBANA, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Lightning struck a cemetery bell tower,
toppling part of the concrete structure onto a homeless man
sleeping inside and killing him, authorities said Friday.
   ``He never had a chance,'' Assistant Fire Chief Richard Dunn
said. ``It appears the first floor fell on him.''
   The victim was identified as Jay Oleson, 22, of Aurora.
