<HEAD>September Will See Gridiron Behind Iron Curtain</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A football game between Illinois and Southern
California universities will take place Sept. 2 in Moscow in the
first such match in the Soviet Union, Tass said Friday.
   A contract was signed Thursday between the U.S. sponsor and the
Soviet economic group Sovintersport to pave the way for the
historic match dubbed ``Glasnost Cup,'' the official news agency
said.
   The game, from Moscow's Dynamo Stadium, will be televised live
