company,'' Tass quoted Kenneth Haines, a representative of the
sponsoring firm Raycom, as saying. ``To bring so many Americans and
to present their favorite sport, is it not a step toward mutual
understanding?''
   Raycom, which arranges telecasts of sports events in the United
States, will provide Soviet TV with videotapes of American football
games to help Soviets understand the game, Haines told Tass.
