<HEAD>Airliner Evacuated After Wheels Catch Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Miami-bound American airliner carrying 147 West
German and Austrian vacationers was evacuated Friday when its
undercarriage caught fire as the plane was taxiing at Stansted
airport near London, officials said.
   They said one unidentified man received minor head injuries as
he slid down an emergency escape chute from the DC-8 of the Pegasus
Holidays company.
   Airport managing director Allan Munds said the passengers and
seven crew ``were never in any danger.''
   The plane had landed to refuel on a flight from Vienna and was
taxiing to the runway for takeoff when two tires burst and flames
blazed up.
   The passengers were taken to hotels to await a replacement
airliner due Saturday, an Independent TV News broadcast said.
