<FIRST>r f BC-BoeingReorganization     04-28 0118</FIRST>
<SECOND>BC-Boeing Reorganization,0123</SECOND>
<HEAD>Boeing Consolidates Aerospace, Electronics Divisions</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SEATTLE (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Boeing Co. on Friday announced a reorganization
in which Boeing Aerospace and Boeing Electronics will become one
division.
   Corporate senior vice president Dan Pinick becomes president of
the new organization, called Boeing Aerospace and Electronics. The
reorganization takes effect Monday.
   The reorganization will involve a variety of military programs,
including the AWACS system, several Boeing-built missiles, NASA
space-station efforts and work on the Strategic Defense Initiative,
known as ``Star Wars.''
   ``In light of the current defense market outlook, it is
particularly important that Boeing take this step to improve
performance on existing government programs, streamline costs of
operations, and improve utilization of all resources,'' Pinick said.
</TEXT>
